Australian fertility data

Source: R/australia.R
aus_fertility.Rd

aus_fertility is an annual `tsibble` covering the years 1921-2002 with three values:

Fertility:Fertility rate per 1000 women
Exposure:Population of women at 30 June each year
Births:Number of births

Format

Time series of class `tsibble`

Source

Australian Human Mortality Database

Details

The data is disaggregated using one key:

Age:Age of mother at time of birth

The extreme age groups (15 and 49) also include a few younger and older mothers respectively.

Examples

library(ggplot2)
aus_fertility
#> # A tsibble: 3,010 x 5 [1Y]
#> # Key:       Age [35]
#>     Year   Age Fertility Exposure Births
#>    <int> <int>     <dbl>    <dbl>  <dbl>
#>  1  1921    15      1.75    49228   86.1
#>  2  1922    15      1.59    50118   79.7
#>  3  1923    15      1.59    51033   81.1
#>  4  1924    15      1.71    51930   88.8
#>  5  1925    15      2.1     52888  111. 
#>  6  1926    15      2.4     53813  129. 
#>  7  1927    15      2.3     54770  126. 
#>  8  1928    15      2.4     55701  134. 
#>  9  1929    15      2.5     56464  141. 
#> 10  1930    15      2.3     57066  131. 
#> # ℹ 3,000 more rows
aus_fertility |>
  rainbow_plot(Fertility) +
  ylab("Fertility rate")
